data.name: Herb-Crusted Rack of Lamb with Ratatouille
data.quickTastyDescription: Succulent rack of lamb coated in aromatic herbs, served with a colorful and flavorful ratatouille.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a small bowl, mix the chopped parsley, rosemary, thyme, minced garlic, olive oil, salt, and pepper to create the herb crust.
Rub the herb mixture all over the rack of lamb.
Place the lamb in a roasting pan and roast for about 25-30 minutes for medium-rare, or until desired doneness.
While the lamb is roasting, heat some olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add the onion and sauté until translucent, about 5 minutes.
Add the zucchini, bell pepper, and eggplant and cook for another 5-7 minutes until softened.
Stir in the diced tomato and balsamic vinegar, and season with salt and pepper. Cook for an additional 5 minutes to blend the flavors.
Once the lamb is done, let it rest for about 5 minutes before slicing.
Serve the sliced lamb alongside the ratatouille.
